        conseils: "Compiègne Palace is open daily except Tuesday, 10am-6pm. Combined ticket for all three museums costs €9.50 (free for under-26 EU residents). The palace park is freely accessible. The Armistice clearing (Armistice Wagon Museum) is 7 km from the centre in the forest (admission €7, open daily except Tuesday). In the forest, Beaux Monts offers the finest viewpoint along a 4 km perspective created for Napoleon I. The town has good restaurants on the Oise riverbank. The Imperial Theatre, a miniature replica of the Paris Opera, opens for special occasions. A combined Compiègne + Pierrefonds excursion is highly recommended as the two sites are only 14 km apart. Allow half a day for Compiègne alone, a full day with Pierrefonds.",
