        description: "The Paris — Thoiry Zoo route takes you to one of France's largest zoological parks, unique for its drive-through safari among free-roaming animals. Located in the Yvelines, 50 km west of Paris, the Thoiry estate combines zoo, safari, Renaissance château and botanical gardens.",
        routeDescription: "The route takes the A13 motorway then the A12 towards Dreux, before joining the D11 to Thoiry through the Yvelines countryside.",
        introduction: "The ZooSafari de Thoiry is a unique zoological park in France, founded in 1968 by Viscount Paul de La Panouse on the family estate of Château de Thoiry. The concept, revolutionary at the time, allowed visitors to drive through reserves where animals live in semi-freedom across vast grassy plains. Today, the car safari extends over 8 km through recreated African savannahs: visitors encounter lions, brown bears, African elephants, white rhinos, giraffes, zebras and wildebeest, separated by double-gate security systems. The walking zoo, covering 60 hectares, presents over 750 animals from 120 species, including a glass tunnel through the lion enclosure and a tropical greenhouse with free-roaming monkeys. The Château de Thoiry, built in 1559 by Philibert de l'Orme, is itself remarkable: it is oriented according to a unique solar alignment that allows the sun to shine through the vestibule from end to end at the summer and winter solstices, creating a 'bridge of light'. The formal French gardens and hedge maze complete this exceptional visit. Getting to Thoiry by TaxiNeo taxi is particularly smart because the safari is done by car: your driver takes you through the enclosures in the comfort of the sedan, without you having to rent a vehicle.",
        itineraire: "Your TaxiNeo driver picks you up at your Paris address and joins the A13 motorway towards Rouen via Porte d'Auteuil or Porte de Saint-Cloud. After crossing the Saint-Cloud viaduct, you branch onto the A12 towards Dreux-Bois d'Arcy. The A12 crosses the Versailles plateau and state forest before reaching the Yvelines countryside. At the Jouars-Pontchartrain exit, the D11 takes you through fields and copses typical of this preserved agricultural region. The village of Thoiry appears nestled between hillsides, with the estate gates clearly signposted. Your driver drops you at the park entrance, or better yet, can directly participate in the car safari, driving through the animal reserves with you aboard. This is a unique advantage of the taxi: you enjoy the safari without driving, free to take photos and videos. In case of traffic on the A13, an alternative route via the A86 then N12 via Trappes is possible, adding only 10 minutes to the journey.",
        conseils: "The ZooSafari de Thoiry is open year-round, from 10am to 5pm in winter and 10am to 6:30pm in summer (last safari entry 1.5 hours before closing). Online tickets are €32 adult and €26 child (3-11), including safari + zoo + château. The car safari takes about 1-1.5 hours depending on speed and stops to observe animals. It's recommended to start the safari at opening when animals are most active. The walking zoo requires an additional 2-3 hours. The château is free to visit and the hedge maze is very popular with children. Several picnic areas are available in the zoo, and the restaurant Le Comptoir de Thoiry offers dishes from €12. Note: convertibles and motorcycles are not allowed in the safari. Plan a full day (10am-5pm) to enjoy the entire estate. Ask your TaxiNeo driver to stay with you for the safari then wait during the walking zoo visit.",
        comparaisonTransport: "There is no direct public transport to Thoiry. By train, Paris Montparnasse → Villiers-Neauphle-Pontchartrain takes 40 minutes (Transilien N, about €8) but then 10 km remain with no regular transport. By rental car, expect €50 per day plus €5 toll and fuel. The drive-through safari makes a car essential, which is the major advantage of TaxiNeo: at €80-100 one way, your driver takes you through the safari, avoiding the stress of driving among lions and elephants. The full-day package with safari and waiting during the walking zoo is about €160, or €40 per person for 4 passengers — excellent value for a unique experience.",
        faq: [
          { question: "How much does a taxi Paris — Thoiry cost?", answer: "The fare is fixed between €80 and €100 one way. We recommend the full-day package with safari and waiting during the walking zoo, from €160. Van (5-7 passengers): €125 one way." },
          { question: "Can the driver go through the safari with us?", answer: "Yes, that's our recommendation! Your TaxiNeo driver drives through the safari enclosures while you enjoy the sights and take photos. This is a unique advantage over driving a rental car yourself." },
          { question: "How much time should I plan for Thoiry?", answer: "Plan a full day: 1-1.5 hours for the car safari, 2-3 hours for the walking zoo, and 30 min to 1 hour for the château and gardens. A 9am departure from Paris and 5pm return are ideal." },
          { question: "Is the zoo open in winter?", answer: "Yes, the ZooSafari de Thoiry is open year-round, including winter (10am-5pm). Animals are visible in all seasons, and the safari remains driveable except in exceptional weather conditions." },
          { question: "Are there restrictions for the car safari?", answer: "Windows must stay closed in carnivore enclosures. Convertibles, motorcycles and campervans are not allowed. TaxiNeo sedans are perfectly suited for the safari route." },
        ],
