        introduction: "Val d'Europe is a major shopping and leisure hub in eastern Paris, located in Serris, just minutes from Disneyland Paris. The shopping centre, opened in 2000 and designed in Haussmann-style architecture with glass roofs and stone facades, houses over 160 brands: Galeries Lafayette, Primark, H&M, Zara, Apple, FNAC, and numerous fashion and home décor shops. Adjacent to the centre, La Vallée Village is an open-air luxury outlet bringing together over 110 designer brand boutiques — Gucci, Prada, Burberry, Sandro, Maje, Longchamp — offering permanent discounts of 30-70% off retail prices. The village has become a destination in its own right, attracting international tourists, particularly from Asia, with personal shopping services and tax refunds for non-EU visitors. Sea Life Paris Val d'Europe aquarium, located in the basement of the shopping centre, is a fascinating 2,500 m² marine world housing over 350 species and 5,000 marine creatures. The immersive route passes through a 360° underwater tunnel where sharks, rays and turtles swim overhead, touch pools where children can feel starfish and anemones, and themed zones from the English Channel to tropical reefs. With a combined shopping + aquarium ticket, Val d'Europe offers a complete day of family entertainment. TaxiNeo taxi is the most comfortable way to get there with children, especially if you plan to return loaded with shopping bags.",
