        itineraire: "Your TaxiNeo driver picks you up at your Paris address. From central Paris, the route takes Rue de Lyon then Avenue Daumesnil, one of the finest boulevards in eastern Paris lined with the Promenade Plantée (predecessor of New York's High Line). After Place de la Nation, you reach Porte Dorée, recognisable by the Palais de la Porte Dorée with its Art Deco facade and tropical aquarium. The entrance to the Bois de Vincennes is immediate. Your driver follows Avenue Daumesnil through the woods, passing Lac Daumesnil and its rowing boats before arriving at the zoo's main entrance on Route de la Ceinture du Lac Daumesnil. Drop-off is directly at the entrance, steps from the ticket office. Alternative from the Right Bank: the eastern ring road via Porte de Charenton or Porte Dorée is equally fast. If you also wish to visit the Château de Vincennes (at the other end of the woods, 3 km away), your driver can take you there in 5 minutes at the end of the day. For a full day in the Bois de Vincennes (zoo, château, Parc Floral, lake), arrange a programme with your driver who can provide transfers between sites.",
